1.] Inheritance - Concept of using the code which is written in another class

2.] Based on the relationship between two classes , we can select the type of relationship required between the two classes 
i.e., A) Aggregation B) Composition 

3.] If the relationship between parent and child class is kind of IS-A relationship, then "Aggregation" is suitable

4.] If the relationship is kind of HAS-A relationship, then "Composition" is suitable

5.] "extends" is the keyword in inheritance aggregation relationship

6.] Parent class constructor can't inherited at child class, Instead of that, super method with same variables is created to access it.

7.] Super class members with Default access is accessible in the child class, only if the parent and child are from same package

8. private variables from super class is accessible through public getters and setters